00:03:46.390 --> 00:03:48.140
Help me make Spica the best team.

00:03:46.390 --> 00:03:50.090
With more shops all over the campus, 
and merch stands at the race tracks,

00:03:48.140 --> 00:03:49.850
I will </i>not<i> lose to her!

00:03:49.850 --> 00:03:52.180
I want to win the Dream Trophy.

00:03:50.090 --> 00:03:54.430
leading into online sales, so that 
I can ultimately expand overseas and...

00:03:52.180 --> 00:03:55.370
I also have a wish from Suzuka-san.

00:03:55.370 --> 00:03:56.530
Safety first...

00:03:56.530 --> 00:04:00.220
For the honor of the Mejiro family, 
I must win a successive spring Tennoushou.

00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:04.790
I'm gonna be an undefeated horse girl!

00:04:05.820 --> 00:04:07.670
You're not supposed to shout your prayers.

00:04:19.010 --> 00:04:20.380
Okay!

00:04:26.690 --> 00:04:28.300
Looking good, Teio!

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:33.270
It all starts here, Teio.

00:04:49.070 --> 00:04:50.820
Look at her kick it up!

00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:52.910
I didn't think she'd be in 
this kind of shape so soon.

00:04:52.910 --> 00:04:55.080
Hell, she might be better than ever.

00:04:59.310 --> 00:05:01.090
Just watch me, Prez!

00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:03.840
I'm gonna make a comeback!

00:05:04.070 --> 00:05:06.590
Trainer-san!

00:05:06.630 --> 00:05:09.550
Hayakawa
Tazuna

00:05:09.570 --> 00:05:11.670
Tazuna-san? What's wrong?

00:05:11.670 --> 00:05:16.940
It's amazing! Teio-san and McQueen-san 
have been selected for the URA Awards!

00:05:17.850 --> 00:05:20.750
You guys, that's amazing!

00:05:21.640 --> 00:05:26.320
We will now be awarding the 
final URA Awards of the year.

00:05:26.320 --> 00:05:28.950
On stage to receive them are 
these two young ladies.

00:05:29.570 --> 00:05:33.250
While she unfortunately missed her chance 
at the Triple Crown, with 134 votes,

00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:37.400
she has been selected as 
Horse Girl of the Year: Tokai Teio-san!

00:05:37.400 --> 00:05:38.710
Yeah!

00:05:39.230 --> 00:05:40.960
Congratulations.

00:05:41.250 --> 00:05:44.120
Although I'm sure there were 
a few pity votes included.

00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:45.640
Say what?

00:05:45.640 --> 00:05:49.720
Including the Spring Tennoushou, she's won 
three races and come in second twice,

00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:51.250
a remarkable record.

00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:53.970
She has been selected as 
Top Senior-Class Horse Girl of the Year.

00:05:53.970 --> 00:05:55.610
Mejiro McQueen-san!

00:05:55.610 --> 00:05:57.500
This is such an honor.

00:05:57.500 --> 00:05:59.230
That's McQueen for you.

00:05:59.230 --> 00:06:01.530
Shame about the Arima Kinen, though.

00:06:01.530 --> 00:06:02.940
What was that?

00:06:02.940 --> 00:06:06.320
Can you two not just give 
sincere compliments?

00:06:07.620 --> 00:06:10.570
Could the two of you give us a 
few words about your upcoming goals?

00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:13.120
My goal's to be undefeated!

00:06:13.120 --> 00:06:16.700
I intend to win a second 
consecutive Spring Tennoushou!

00:06:19.080 --> 00:06:23.500
To reflect their accomplishments, they are 
both being provided with new racing wear.

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:24.590
Awesome!

00:06:24.590 --> 00:06:25.790
Thank you very much.

00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:29.050
Everyone is going to be looking forward 
to your performances this year!

00:06:29.050 --> 00:06:31.170
Let's give them a big round of applause!

00:06:35.230 --> 00:06:37.850
Who do you think would win if they raced?

00:06:37.850 --> 00:06:39.600
Teio, probably.

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:41.770
Nah, I think it'd be McQueen.

00:06:41.770 --> 00:06:44.230
Makes you wanna see how it'd turn out.

00:06:45.020 --> 00:06:48.530
We may even see these two compete 
against each other, this year.

00:06:54.740 --> 00:06:57.740
URA AWARD <font color="#d71894">WINNERS NAMED!</font>

00:06:55.860 --> 00:06:58.020
Wow, Spica!

00:06:58.020 --> 00:06:59.920
I guess Spica's the top team now.

00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:02.030
Meanwhile, our team is...

00:07:02.030 --> 00:07:04.660
We keep coming close, but...

00:07:04.660 --> 00:07:07.000
Doesn't that bug you, trainer?!

00:07:07.210 --> 00:07:11.630
I'd say it does. It'd be wonderful if 
we could prove what we were capable of.

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:14.820
I say Canopus' goal is to beat Spica!

00:07:14.820 --> 00:07:16.380
I don't think that's—

00:07:15.450 --> 00:07:17.420
An excellent objective.

00:07:17.420 --> 00:07:18.970
Down with Spica!

00:07:18.970 --> 00:07:20.320
Here we go!

00:07:20.320 --> 00:07:21.580
Yeah!

00:07:21.580 --> 00:07:22.600
Yeah?

00:07:22.600 --> 00:07:25.360
Time to declare war on Spica!

00:07:25.580 --> 00:07:27.890
Down with Spica!

00:07:27.890 --> 00:07:30.430
Down with Spica!

00:07:30.430 --> 00:07:32.610
Wouldn't it be better to train?

00:07:33.450 --> 00:07:36.700
Spica

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:36.700
Looks like everyone is 
gunning for Spica this year.

00:07:36.700 --> 00:07:40.490
Everyone's gonna be coming 
at us, so stay on your toes.

00:07:42.830 --> 00:07:45.040
The letter arrow worked perfectly!

00:07:45.270 --> 00:07:47.460
Retreat!

00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:47.460
Run away!

00:07:45.730 --> 00:07:47.460
Why did I come along?

00:07:47.460 --> 00:07:50.140
Trainer! They shot a letter arrow at us!

00:07:50.140 --> 00:07:51.600
What?! Read it out!

00:07:51.600 --> 00:07:52.370
Okay!

00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:55.470
Drown with Spica!
—Turbo

00:07:53.750 --> 00:07:55.470
"Drown with Spica!"

00:07:56.040 --> 00:07:57.810
Is that spelled wrong?

00:07:57.810 --> 00:07:59.580
So they're declaring war on us?

00:07:59.580 --> 00:08:02.850
I guess we'll have to show them 
who's boss at the racetrack.

00:08:02.850 --> 00:08:04.890
Exactly. When you're considered 
the top competitors,

00:08:04.890 --> 00:08:07.450
you have to work hard 
to maintain that esteem.

00:08:07.450 --> 00:08:10.520
Which means, Teio, 
as far as your comeback goes—

00:08:10.520 --> 00:08:11.490
Trainer...

00:08:12.460 --> 00:08:14.990
I want to enter the Spring Tennoushou.

00:08:17.740 --> 00:08:21.370
My goal is to continue being undefeated.

00:08:21.370 --> 00:08:26.870
But I don't think that will mean anything 
unless I take on strong competition.

00:08:26.870 --> 00:08:27.710
So...

00:08:29.460 --> 00:08:31.930
That'd mean Teio and McQueen...

00:08:31.930 --> 00:08:35.200
You guys okay with potentially 
ruining each other's plans?

00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:37.860
I gladly accept the challenge.

00:08:37.860 --> 00:08:41.850
I expected to race against you someday.

00:08:42.150 --> 00:08:44.170
There's no problem, is there, Trainer-san?

00:08:44.170 --> 00:08:45.300
Are you two serious?

00:08:45.300 --> 00:08:47.170
I'm gonna be the one who achieves her goal.

00:08:47.170 --> 00:08:49.290
Because I'm not gonna lose 
to you either, McQueen!

00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:52.340
And I have no intention of 
allowing you to win, Teio.

00:08:52.340 --> 00:08:54.320
I will win a consecutive Tennoushou!

00:08:54.320 --> 00:08:55.600
Have it your way.

00:08:55.600 --> 00:09:00.070
In that case, Teio's gonna be running 
in the Osaka Hai before the Tennoushou.

00:09:00.070 --> 00:09:00.910
Yeah!

00:09:00.910 --> 00:09:04.670
And before the Tennoushou, McQueen, 
you need to take on the Hanshin Daishoten.

00:09:04.670 --> 00:09:05.870
Understood.

00:09:05.870 --> 00:09:08.500
I expect both of you to give 
this everything you've got!

00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:09.590
Right!

00:09:09.590 --> 00:09:11.940
And don't go telling anyone about this yet.

00:09:11.940 --> 00:09:12.300
Got it.

00:09:12.790 --> 00:09:14.510
I got it, all right!

00:09:14.510 --> 00:09:16.540
Everyone is going to know now.

00:09:16.540 --> 00:09:17.600
Man...

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:20.590
A race between members of Spica, huh?

