00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:34.360
TEIO AND MCQUEEN RACING AGAINST EACH OTHER!?

00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:35.550
The undefeated horse girl, Tokai Teio,

00:09:35.550 --> 00:09:38.360
and the senior-class award-winning 
horse girl, Mejiro McQueen,

00:09:38.360 --> 00:09:39.990
will be clashing at the Tennoushou...

00:09:40.260 --> 00:09:43.290
As announced by Team Spica, 
which represents both competitors.

00:09:48.040 --> 00:09:49.670
She's really motivated!

00:09:49.670 --> 00:09:52.040
How many times does that make?

00:09:52.270 --> 00:09:53.880
Looking good, McQueen!

00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:55.420
Goal

00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:55.940
Increase your pace a bit more!

00:09:59.680 --> 00:10:02.200
Damn, that's a long stretch!

00:10:03.070 --> 00:10:04.350
Teio!

00:10:04.350 --> 00:10:06.100
Don't get sloppy with your form!

00:10:06.420 --> 00:10:08.770
I know!

00:10:17.320 --> 00:10:19.070
Goal

00:10:23.510 --> 00:10:25.210
That wasn't hard at all!

00:10:25.210 --> 00:10:27.250
All too easy, frankly.

00:10:29.370 --> 00:10:33.000
<u>Down with</u> Spica!
Strategy Meeting

00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:33.000
Now, then, it's time for 
today's strategy meeting.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:34.200
Yeah!

00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:35.550
Yeah...

00:10:35.550 --> 00:10:39.530
Our subject today: How do 
we avoid losing to Spica?

00:10:39.940 --> 00:10:41.760
Yes, Twin Turbo-san?

00:10:41.760 --> 00:10:42.880
We come in first place!

00:10:42.880 --> 00:10:44.980
True, yes, but what else?

00:10:44.980 --> 00:10:46.530
Uh... don't come in second!

00:10:46.530 --> 00:10:47.800
Does that mean third is fine?

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:49.040
We can also avoid racing them!

00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:50.520
We won't lose that way, 
but we also won't win!

00:10:50.520 --> 00:10:51.980
There's also running hard!

00:10:51.980 --> 00:10:54.020
I guess that works, if it helps you win.

00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:56.150
But at the last Arima Kinen...

00:10:56.150 --> 00:10:59.150
Number 12, Twin Turbo, is setting 
a fast early pace, like she said.

00:10:56.150 --> 00:10:59.150
<font color="#4493d0" size="21">Twin Turbo</font>

00:10:59.490 --> 00:11:01.490
I've got this! I've got this!

00:11:02.300 --> 00:11:06.570
And McQueen shocks us all 
by coming in second place!

00:11:04.930 --> 00:11:05.890
<font size="21" color="#6880b4">Daitaku Helios</font>

00:11:13.580 --> 00:11:15.520
It just didn't kick in that time!

00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:16.460
What didn't?

00:11:17.300 --> 00:11:19.600
What've you been looking at, Ikuno?

00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:22.680
Ikuno's running against 
Teio at the Osaka Hai.

00:11:23.040 --> 00:11:24.490
Tokai Teio...

00:11:24.930 --> 00:11:29.180
I'll analyze every aspect of her racing,
 and find a way to beat her.

00:11:30.510 --> 00:11:32.040
We should work hard, too!

00:11:32.040 --> 00:11:33.440
Yeah! This calls for more meetings!

00:11:33.690 --> 00:11:34.800
Yeah!

00:11:34.800 --> 00:11:37.690
Um... you could train instead 
of having meetings.

00:11:37.690 --> 00:11:40.110
Honey, honey, honey!

00:11:40.110 --> 00:11:43.550
When I get a taste of that honey...

00:11:44.430 --> 00:11:45.510
Is that...

00:11:46.190 --> 00:11:48.860
Here you go. Soft, light, 
and easy on the honey.

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:50.070
McQueen?

00:11:50.500 --> 00:11:52.210
That'll be 1,000 yen.

00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:53.850
What a coincidence.

00:11:53.850 --> 00:11:55.350
Yeah, I guess so.

00:11:59.620 --> 00:12:01.050
So good!

00:12:01.050 --> 00:12:04.360
McQueen, you must've been 
training late today, huh?

00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:07.310
I could ask you the same thing. You're sure 
you're not overworking yourself?

00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:08.800
Right back at you.

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:13.800
I must say, it's been quite a while 
since I walked home with you.

00:12:13.800 --> 00:12:15.180
It has?

00:12:15.180 --> 00:12:19.070
When I first met you, I remember you 
following me around quite a bit.

00:12:19.370 --> 00:12:22.020
You were just being too self-conscious.

00:12:22.020 --> 00:12:23.860
It's been that way ever 
since the entrance ceremony.

00:12:28.300 --> 00:12:30.200
Entrance Ceremony

00:12:32.170 --> 00:12:33.670
Is she the one everyone's talking about?

00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:34.960
Tokai Teio-san?

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:37.290
Yeah! She's supposed to be really fast.

00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:39.140
Let's all have a good time here!

00:12:51.560 --> 00:12:54.100
It's a pleasure to be attending 
school with all of you.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:58.900
You can tell she's from the Mejiro family.

00:12:58.900 --> 00:13:00.970
And she's supposed to be a great racer, too.

00:13:02.940 --> 00:13:04.950
She's pretty cool!

00:13:04.950 --> 00:13:08.320
New students are always united 
in their thoughts and desires,

00:13:08.320 --> 00:13:10.340
while each having their distinct resolve,

00:13:10.340 --> 00:13:15.660
which I hope will be a source of 
boundless determination for all of you.

00:13:15.660 --> 00:13:17.040
Congratulations on your enrollment.

00:13:20.090 --> 00:13:21.690
That's the Prez for you!

00:13:21.690 --> 00:13:24.920
And now, representing the new class...

00:13:24.920 --> 00:13:26.970
An address from Mejiro McQueen-san.

00:13:26.970 --> 00:13:29.800
Huh? It's the girl from before.

00:13:31.020 --> 00:13:36.030
As of today, we horse girls have 
become students at Tracen Academy,

00:13:36.030 --> 00:13:40.840
where our new lives will begin, 
like the budding of cherry blossoms.

00:13:40.840 --> 00:13:43.430
As we dedicate ourselves to our 
daily learning and training,

00:13:43.430 --> 00:13:48.070
we will now be running the same 
halls as our great forebears....

00:13:45.010 --> 00:13:48.070
She's trying to show off 
in front of the Prez!

00:13:54.230 --> 00:13:56.920
McQueen, that's quite the time you managed!

00:13:56.920 --> 00:13:59.080
Yes, naturally.

00:14:00.710 --> 00:14:02.380
That was incredible, Teio!

00:14:06.320 --> 00:14:07.880
Impressive.

00:14:08.430 --> 00:14:09.890
You want to hang out before heading home?

00:14:10.100 --> 00:14:12.500
Yeah! I could really go for some steak!

00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:14.000
Gotta be steak!

00:14:39.330 --> 00:14:41.540
Would you stop already?

00:14:41.540 --> 00:14:43.790
Could you please put an end to this?

00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:45.450
Enough!

00:14:45.450 --> 00:14:46.880
No more!

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:49.170
Ow, ow, ow...

00:14:52.290 --> 00:14:55.310
O-Oh, you're from the class next door.

00:14:55.310 --> 00:14:57.060
Wh-What a coincidence.

00:14:57.060 --> 00:14:58.720
Y-Yes, it must be.

00:14:58.720 --> 00:15:00.810
Were you training this late?

00:15:00.810 --> 00:15:02.330
I-I could ask you the same thing.

00:15:02.330 --> 00:15:03.190
Yes...

00:15:03.190 --> 00:15:06.450
You certainly seem tired! Are you alright?

00:15:06.450 --> 00:15:09.900
Nope, I'm fine! I'm curious, 
what's that you're carrying?

00:15:09.900 --> 00:15:11.780
I-It's nothing important!

00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:13.580
I-I see!

00:15:14.710 --> 00:15:16.290
Th-That's right.

00:15:17.830 --> 00:15:19.410
The Next Day

00:15:19.540 --> 00:15:21.160
The Day After That

00:15:21.290 --> 00:15:23.210
And the Day After That

00:15:29.790 --> 00:15:31.160
What a coincidence.

00:15:31.160 --> 00:15:32.550
I suppose so.

00:15:36.720 --> 00:15:40.930
We had quite a string of coincidences 
before joining Spica.

00:15:40.930 --> 00:15:41.560
Yeah.

00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:55.230
The cherry blossoms will be blooming soon.

00:15:56.080 --> 00:15:56.780
Yep.

00:16:00.080 --> 00:16:03.980
There's a steady rain today 
at the Hanshin Racecourse,

00:16:03.980 --> 00:16:06.210
casting a dark pall over the track.

00:16:06.210 --> 00:16:10.090
This is the first race of the year for our 
most popular competitor, Mejiro McQueen.

00:16:10.090 --> 00:16:11.440
It should be an interesting one.

00:16:11.440 --> 00:16:12.400
McQueen!

00:16:14.400 --> 00:16:17.350
The rain is nasty today. 
Be careful of the mud, all right?

00:16:17.350 --> 00:16:19.790
You needn't warn me, I assure you.

00:16:19.790 --> 00:16:23.240
It was raining during the fall Tennoushou 
last year as well, wasn't it?

00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:24.070
You nervous?

00:16:24.070 --> 00:16:26.690
Hardly. If anything, I'm glad.

00:16:26.690 --> 00:16:28.990
Things are different now.

00:16:28.990 --> 00:16:32.130
I intend to run hard enough 
to blow the rain away.

00:16:41.830 --> 00:16:44.050
There are only six running in this race?

00:16:44.050 --> 00:16:47.930
I guess it's only natural, 
with how strong McQueen looks lately.

00:16:47.930 --> 00:16:50.330
They've all got McQueen marked.

00:16:50.330 --> 00:16:51.930
It's practically five-on-one.

00:16:51.930 --> 00:16:53.960
You got this, McQueen!

00:16:57.890 --> 00:16:59.830
Where are you going, Teio-san?

00:16:59.830 --> 00:17:03.530
I'm gonna just check out the course 
for when I run in the Osaka Hai.

00:17:04.370 --> 00:17:07.730
Good luck, McQueen-san!

00:17:09.070 --> 00:17:10.500
Teio-san's here!

00:17:11.050 --> 00:17:12.850
Teio-san!

00:17:11.050 --> 00:17:13.860
Kita-chan! We're here to 
root for McQueen-san today!

00:17:13.860 --> 00:17:18.270
The horse girls have finished their warm-ups,
 and are headed to the gate.

00:17:16.240 --> 00:17:17.420
Okay.

00:17:33.750 --> 00:17:36.580
Well! Guess I was worried for nothing.

00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:37.880
Teio?

00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:40.030
Cheering from beside the course today?

00:17:40.030 --> 00:17:42.500
Nope! Just wanted to get a good look at it.

00:17:42.500 --> 00:17:46.550
You must be awfully confident, 
worrying about me.

00:17:46.550 --> 00:17:47.640
I could say the same to you!

00:17:47.640 --> 00:17:49.940
I hope you're all right with 
me getting ahead of you,

00:17:49.940 --> 00:17:51.220
winning this race and all.

00:17:51.220 --> 00:17:52.470
Knock yourself out!

00:17:52.470 --> 00:17:56.370
Just be sure to watch when I win the 
Osaka Hai. Because I will win it!

00:18:16.050 --> 00:18:18.140
The horse girls are at the gate.

00:18:18.140 --> 00:18:21.270
As the rain falls on them, 
they wait for the start.

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:27.100
Even if they all come after me...
 I'll accept the challenge.

00:18:27.100 --> 00:18:28.020
We can do this!

00:18:28.020 --> 00:18:30.770
The Hanshin Daishoten, 
a course of 3,000 meters...

00:18:32.150 --> 00:18:33.400
has just begun!

00:18:36.620 --> 00:18:39.400
At 3,000 meters, this is a long 
race with a small roster!

00:18:39.740 --> 00:18:41.930
It opens things up for 
some interesting tactics!

00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:43.660
All right, that's a good start!

00:18:45.660 --> 00:18:48.270
They're turning the third 
corner of the first lap.

00:18:48.270 --> 00:18:51.790
With the persistent rain, the track 
is likely to be on the heavy side.

00:18:51.790 --> 00:18:54.790
I need to make sure to take every step 
steadily and securely to stay on my feet!

00:18:55.050 --> 00:18:58.800
If I can maintain my racing style, 
no one should be able to beat me!

00:18:58.800 --> 00:19:00.800
Just like this! Just like this!

00:19:00.800 --> 00:19:02.220
The racers are now through the fourth corner

00:19:02.220 --> 00:19:04.720
and entering the home 
stretch of the first lap.

00:19:04.720 --> 00:19:06.250
Go, McQueen!

00:19:06.250 --> 00:19:07.220
Go!

00:19:07.220 --> 00:19:09.330
Even in this heavy rain, there are 
a lot of spectators here today

00:19:09.330 --> 00:19:12.800
rooting for these horse girls, 
including Mejiro McQueen!

00:19:11.730 --> 00:19:13.940
Wow! They're all secure in their positions!

00:19:12.800 --> 00:19:15.230
Now, all six competitors 
have formed up again!

00:19:13.940 --> 00:19:15.230
McQueen-san!

00:19:15.590 --> 00:19:19.490
McQueen, who is aiming to win the 
spring Tennoushou, is currently in third place!

00:19:19.490 --> 00:19:21.610
She's in a good position, and staying steady.

00:19:21.610 --> 00:19:27.570
And right behind Mejiro McQueen, 
not giving an inch, is #5, Kania Curation!

00:19:27.570 --> 00:19:31.580
She's positioned behind McQueen, 
ready to make her move at any moment!

00:19:29.150 --> 00:19:30.990
Things are looking good.

00:19:30.990 --> 00:19:33.650
Of course they are. 
It's McQueen who's running.

00:19:34.090 --> 00:19:35.210
I guess you're right.

00:19:35.210 --> 00:19:37.160
I thought they'd be coming after her harder!

00:19:37.160 --> 00:19:39.210
But at this rate, it should be no problem.

00:19:39.210 --> 00:19:40.720
They've entered the second lap.

00:19:41.400 --> 00:19:44.460
Kania Curation is moving 
up from behind McQueen!

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:46.050
All right, it looks like I can do this!

00:19:46.050 --> 00:19:46.820
I can do this!

00:19:46.820 --> 00:19:47.930
I can do this!

00:19:48.880 --> 00:19:49.590
I can do this!

00:19:49.590 --> 00:19:50.270
I can do this!

00:19:50.270 --> 00:19:51.520
What's this?!

00:19:51.520 --> 00:19:54.550
It looks like the other horse girls are 
all starting to close in on McQueen!

00:19:51.910 --> 00:19:52.580
I can do this!

00:19:52.580 --> 00:19:53.190
I can do this!

00:19:53.190 --> 00:19:53.810
I can do this!

00:19:53.810 --> 00:19:54.550
I can do this!

00:19:54.550 --> 00:19:55.270
I can do this!

00:19:56.090 --> 00:19:57.770
This is quite a bit of pressure.

00:19:57.770 --> 00:19:59.500
They've all got her marked!

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:00.490
McQueen-san...

00:20:01.210 --> 00:20:02.810
You just had to jinx it, didn't you?

00:20:02.810 --> 00:20:04.820
You're the one who brought it up!

00:20:04.820 --> 00:20:05.780
Go!

00:20:06.050 --> 00:20:09.290
They've rounded the third corner, 
and are entering the fourth!

00:20:10.120 --> 00:20:13.410
From here, I can catch her!

00:20:13.410 --> 00:20:14.670
I can catch her!

00:20:14.670 --> 00:20:15.920
I can catch her!

00:20:15.920 --> 00:20:17.420
I can catch her!

00:20:20.430 --> 00:20:22.000
I can totally do this!

00:20:23.230 --> 00:20:24.310
I can catch her!

00:20:24.310 --> 00:20:25.050
Here we go.

00:20:25.050 --> 00:20:27.730
And McQueen makes her move!
 She's going for it!

00:20:27.730 --> 00:20:29.540
Mejiro McQueen has started her spurt!

00:20:29.540 --> 00:20:31.440
She's gaining distance 
on the other horse girls!

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:32.030
Wha—?!

00:20:32.030 --> 00:20:33.730
Go for it, McQueen!

00:20:33.730 --> 00:20:34.980
Wow!

00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:38.120
They're on the last stretch, 
and McQueen has quickly taken the lead!

00:20:38.120 --> 00:20:41.190
But at the same time, 
Kania Curation is moving in behind her!

00:20:41.190 --> 00:20:45.450
Are we looking at a contest between
 Mejiro McQueen and Kania Curation?!

00:20:46.010 --> 00:20:47.950
Not yet... Not yet...

00:20:48.250 --> 00:20:50.580
This is where... This is where...

00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:55.000
I-I can't—!

00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:57.120
We are not! This is not the 
showdown it looked like!

00:20:57.120 --> 00:20:59.130
Mejiro McQueen has gained 
a lead and keeps going!

00:20:59.130 --> 00:21:00.850
Mejiro McQueen is dashing 
toward another confrontation

00:21:00.850 --> 00:21:02.900
at the spring Tennoushou!

00:21:02.510 --> 00:21:04.090
She's amazing!

00:21:02.900 --> 00:21:04.090
Her lead is only getting bigger!

00:21:04.090 --> 00:21:06.140
This is completely one-sided!

00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:09.510
And Mejiro McQueen clears the goal!

00:21:14.210 --> 00:21:17.520
She's left the second place 
finish five lengths behind her!

00:21:17.520 --> 00:21:18.450
Hell yeah!

00:21:18.450 --> 00:21:19.900
She did it!

00:21:21.900 --> 00:21:23.970
McQueen-san!

00:21:23.970 --> 00:21:26.430
I'm really looking forward 
to her race with Teio.

00:21:26.430 --> 00:21:27.680
Tell me about it!

00:21:27.680 --> 00:21:30.150
But I think McQueen's got the edge.

00:21:30.150 --> 00:21:32.540
I mean, after the way she blew the 
second place runner away, yeah!

00:21:32.540 --> 00:21:36.280
I thought so, too! You've got a great eye!

00:21:36.280 --> 00:21:38.340
Teio-san's better, though.

00:21:38.340 --> 00:21:39.900
No, McQueen-san!

00:21:39.900 --> 00:21:41.170
Teio-san!

00:21:48.270 --> 00:21:50.800
McQueen really is tough.

00:21:50.800 --> 00:21:51.740
Teio?

00:21:51.740 --> 00:21:54.770
Trainer, I'm going to impress
you at the Osaka Hai.

00:21:55.490 --> 00:21:56.200
Do it!

00:22:03.360 --> 00:22:05.580
It's your turn next.

00:22:07.110 --> 00:22:08.810
I'm not gonna lose, either.

00:23:36.920 --> 00:23:39.620
Everyone has been waiting for her return.

00:23:39.990 --> 00:23:44.500
The Twin Crown horse girl is now making 
her presence felt at the Osaka Hai!

00:23:45.140 --> 00:23:47.700
In the second bracket, #2, 
the most anticipated competitor...

00:23:48.750 --> 00:23:50.560
Tokai Teio!

00:23:51.305 --> 00:24:51.356
Do you want subtitles for any video?
